Metadata API

Access more metadata through these new and changed metadata types.

Data Processing Engine
Configure CSV delimitation, file identification, directory referencing, and file sourcing for BatchCalcJobDatasource
Use the new csvDelimiter, fileIdentifier, filePath, fileSource fields on the existing BatchCalcJobDatasource metadata subtype of BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 61.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Define input field data types and primary key for CSV data sources
Use the new dataType and isPrimaryKey fields on the existing BatchCalcJobDatasourceField metadata subtype of BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 61.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Enable batch calculation job to use new object for the source object field
Use the new DataLakeObject value in the existing type field on the BatchCalcJobDatasource metadata subtype of the BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 60.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Specify an external field ID for the target object name
Use the new externalIdFieldName field on the existing BatchCalcJobWritebackObject metadata subtype of BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 61.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Add file identifier data type options in batch calculation job parameters
Use the new FileIdentifier value in the existing dataType field on the BatchCalcJobParameter metadata subtype of the BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 60.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Enable overwrite option for batch calculation job writeback objects
Use the new Overwrite value in the existing operationType field on the BatchCalcJobWritebackObject metadata subtype of the BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 60.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Expand process types with BenefitManagement for batch calculations
Use the new BenefitManagement value in the existing processType field on the BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 60.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
Add a new platform to run the Data Processing Engine definition
Use the new CORE value in the existing executionPlatformType field on the BatchCalcJobDefinition metadata type. Introduced in API version 60.0, this field has been added to the Industries Common Resource Developer Guide.
